stix:STIX_Header.stix:Title: Compilation of APT\'s Malicious Tools and Network Infrastructure
stix:STIX_Header.stix:Description: This update was issued on August 12, 2014 to update the IP Indicators.US-CERT has compiled indicators from 3 separate intrusion incidents believed to be from the same actors during 2014. Several domains and IPs were seen at all three affected sites and a few files with identical MD5s were common to two or more of the incidents, as well.Snort Rules created:alert tcp $EXTERNAL_NET $HTTP_PORTS -> $HOME_NET any (msg:"[CCIRC] Possible SWF used in IE 0 Day (CVE-2014-1776)"; flow:established,to_client; file_data; content:"embed src=20140319.swf"; sid:4000033; rev:0;)alert tcp $EXTERNAL_NET $HTTP_PORTS -> $HOME_NET any (msg:"[CCIRC] Suspicious function used in IE 0 days - CVE-2014-0322 and CVE-2014-1776"; flow:established,to_client; file_data; content:"function dword2data"; sid:4000034; rev:0;)alert tcp $HOME_NET any -> $EXTERNAL_NET $HTTP_PORTS (msg:"[CCIRC] IePorxyv Trojan C2 Check-In"; flow:established,to_server; content:"/xdot/index33_0.html"; http_uri; content:"GET"; http_method; sid:4000035; rev:0;)Yara Rules Created:rule IePorxyv_Trojan : APT{meta:id = 70author = "CCIRC"revision = 1date = "May 1 2014"description = "Detects strings found in dll downloaded from IE 0 Day CVE-2014-1776 sample "reference_hash = "Based on sample MD5: 7487d63b7dc5417d1212fab24631df0d"strings:$dllname = "IePorxyv.dll"$export1 = "IePramGet"$export2 = "IeSet"condition:all of them}rule apt_pirpi_new {meta:description = "W32 Pirpi Downloader used in targeted attacks"date = "30/04/2014"hash1 = "3a6e52158c579760556a8e1d2f7f21f3"strings:$s0 = "abcdefhirstuvwxz"$s1 = "%sindex%2.2d_%d.html"$s2 = "vv;expires = Sat,01-Jan-2000 00:00:00 GMT"$s3 = "expand \"%s\" \"%s\""condition:3 of ($s*)}rule exploited_CVE_2014_1776 : WER CVE20141776{meta:author = "MalwrSignatures"date = "2014/05/01"description = "Detects a Internet Explorer Crash Report suspected to be caused by CVE-2014-1776"ref = "http://community.websense.com/blogs/securitylabs/archive/2014/04/28/cve-2014-1776-using-crash-reports-to-find-possible-exploited-vulnerabilities.aspx"filetype = "wer"strings:$exec = /Sig\[[0-9]+\]\.Name=Application Name[\n\r]+Sig\[[0-9]+\]\.Value=iexplore\.exe/ wide nocase$modu = /Sig\[[0-9]+\]\.Name=Fault Module Name[\n\r]+Sig\[[0-9]+\]\.Value=VGX\.DLL/ wide nocase$time = /EventTime=13[89]/ wide nocasecondition:all of them}Previous related IBs:IB-13-10405IB-13-10417IB-14-10230IB-14-10235IB-14-10259IB-14-20079IB-14-20092The following is a listing of this APT’s malicious tools and network infrastructure identified to have been used during recent intrusion campaigns. These indicators can be leveraged by Computer Network Defense (CND) teams for implementation to detect malicious activity by this APT group.
